  <h4><a name="h.va2binilhyot" id="h.va2binilhyot"></a>How to get to
  the trailhead</h3>

  <p>The Kepler Track is easily accessible from the Lake Te Anau control
  gates, either by road or a 45 minute walk from the Fiordland National Park Visitor
  Centre in Te Anau, or over the swing bridge across the Waiau River at Rainbow Reach. A
  shuttle bus also operates during the summer season to entry and exit points on the
  track and a scheduled boat service provides access to Brod Bay.</p>

   

